# V3.1 FRONTEND: THE EHR SIMULATOR (SMART-on-FHIR Ready)

This plan outlines the frontend deployment of a pristine, high-fidelity "EHR Simulator" that maps live V3.1 FHIR/MCP data to professional medical dashboard components via Stich MCP and 21st.dev assets. The simulation emphasizes medical safety constraints ("UI-UX Pro Max"), zero broken links, and real-time Clinical Intelligence visibility in a dedicated 30% width Sidecar.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - Ensure you agree with the 21st.dev component manifest outline.
> - Verify the V4 Test & Validation Matrix covers all critical Hit-in-the-Loop workflows.

## 1. Data-to-Design Mapping Report (Stich MCP Output)

**Phase 0 Alignment Check:**
The `ClinicalIntelligenceData` Pydantic model dictates the UI required in the intelligence hub. Key fields include:
- `original`: Raw text extracted from FHIR resources (Mapped to Source Data View).
- `system` & `mapped_icd10`: Suggested code (Mapped to ICD-10 Search & Suggestion Cards).
- `hcc_data` (`hcc_impact`, `category`, `weight`, `description`): (Mapped to HCC Impact Badges).

**FHIR Data Bridge Mapping:**
- **Observation:** `valueQuantity` and `effectiveDateTime` mapped to **Vital Charts**.
- **Condition:** `code` mapped to **Interactive Diagnosis List** in the main patient view.

## 2. High-Fidelity UI Component Manifest (21st.dev Assets)

Components exclusively sourced from verified, medical-grade 21st.dev assets:
- **Main Patient Dashboard (70% Width):**
  - **Vitals Overview Hero:** High-contrast visualization. Applies status color-coding (e.g., Red for Critical Out-of-Bounds).
  - **Diagnosis Table:** Touch-optimized rows (>44px touch targets).

- **Intelligence Hub Sidecar (30% Width):**
  - **The "EHR Digital Twin" Layout Logic:** Designed to ensure the sidebar doesn't collapse on smaller screens.
    - Used Tailwind classes: `w-[30%] min-w-[350px] sticky top-0 h-screen overflow-y-auto`
  - **Semantic Search Bar:** Connects to `/api/v3/icd10/suggest`.
  - **Clinical Validation Form:** Populates the `ClinicalValidation` model for HITL approval.

## 3. Atomic React Service Layer & Interactive Logic

- **API Client:** Use Axios in `src/services/api.ts` to explicitly define the structure and prevent CORS/header mismatches.
  - Include the `X-API-KEY` in the common headers.
  - Expose a `getSemanticSuggestions(query: string)` function that internally implements a **300ms debounce logic** to safeguard backend traffic and improve UX.
- **Data Binding:** Real-time updates push `ClinicalIntelligenceData` structures directly into React state. 
- **The "Approve & Add to Chart" Workflow:** Submits the `ClinicalValidation` model (with fields `code`, `status`, `clinician_id`, `timestamp`) accurately back to the V3.1 FHIR bridge.

## 4. Pristine Experience Checklist (Zero-Broken-Link Policy)

- [ ] **Touch Targets:** All interactive elements must exceed Apple/Google accessibility guidelines (>44px padding/margin combinations).
- [ ] **Color Theory:** Strict application of high-contrast modes for readable clinical settings.
- [ ] **Refined Error & Empty States:**
  - `SuggestionCard` component handles three explicit states: **Loading**, **Success (Data)**, and **No Results**.
  - If `results.length === 0`, render a card stating *"No clinical matches found. Try a different term or manual entry"* with a high-contrast info icon.
- [ ] **Error/Empty States:** Explicit "Coming Soon" or defined feedback overlays for features not fully implemented to ensure zero perceived broken links.

## 5. Local Execution & Hosting Guide (Vercel + Python Backend)

- **Frontend Hosting (Vercel):** Seamless continuous deployment connected to the React + Tailwind framework repository.
- **Backend Connection:** Environment variables strict locked to the V3.1 Dual-Protocol Hub (`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000/api/v3`).

